c: 6
v: 136
t: "They allocate a share from God's own created fields and cattle to God, and they say: \"This is God's\" -- or so they think -- \"and that, of the compeers of God,\" so that what belongs to the compeers does not reach God, but that which is God's may reach the compeers (set up by them). How bad is the judgement that they make"